│ returns nullptr for loops with multiple exit paths, the correct fix is to   │
│ add the null check as described.                                            │
│                                                                             │
│ The patch addresses the general case described in the root cause analysis,  │
│ even if this specific reproducer might have additional complexities. The    │
│ fix ensures that when `getUniqueExitBlock()` returns nullptr (for loops     │
│ with multiple exit blocks), the vectorizer handles it gracefully by         │
│ connecting directly to the scalar preheader and avoiding the creation of an │
│ invalid VPIRBasicBlock.                                                     │
│                                                                             │
